Three volunteers from Spark, based at Sunderland University’s St Peter’s Campus, have been nominated in the prestigious Student Radio Awards. Jonny Chambers, Alex Burgess and Dom Stirling will attend a ceremony at London’s O2 Arena next month in the hope of scooping a host of gongs at the awards, which helped launch the career of Radio 1 star Greg James Jonny, 19, from Moorside, is in line for the Best Male Presenter in UK Student Radio; Alex, 20, from South Shields, for the Best Female Presenter in UK Student Radio and Dom, from Blackpool, for Best Newcomer in UK Student Radio.